verbose_text: Activation of STING-TBK1 signaling axis after cytosolic dsDNA stimulation leads to the production of type I IFNs, which initiate an innate antiviral response by inducing hundreds of ISGs through the JAK-STAT pathway.
evidence: STING-TBK1 signaling axis after cytosolic dsDNA stimulation leads to the production of type I IFNs
